    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-05-20T08:02:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-05-20T08:02:00-05:00" n="347"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/5–2052: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Office of the United States High Commissioner for
                            Germany</gloss>, at Bonn</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d347fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BARNARDJL1"
                            >Barnard</persName> of <gloss target="#t_RA1">RA</gloss>. Repeated to
                        Brussels, The Hague, London, Paris, and Luxembourg.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-05-20T09:02:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1952—9:02 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3256. Fol highlights <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> Mins mtg Paris May
                        19–20<note n="2" xml:id="d347fn2">See editorial note, <ref target="#pg_618"
                            >p. 618</ref>.</note> as reported by <gloss target="#t_telecon1"
                        >telecon</gloss> to Dept: <pb facs="0708" n="664" xml:id="pg_664"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>1)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Signing Date:</hi> Owing to scheduled <persName
                                corresp="#p_VANZEELAND1">Van Zeeland</persName> and <persName
                                corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName> speeches at Council of
                            Eur on May 26, <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> Treaty and <gloss
                                target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                                >NATO</gloss> protocols cannot be signed until Tues May 27.</item>
                        <label>2)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ger Fin Contribution:</hi> All Mins agreed with
                                <persName corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName> that they shld
                            have opportunity discuss and reach decisions basis latest drafts of
                            Contractuals. Question re Ger Fin contribution therefore placed end of
                            agenda.</item>
                        <label>3)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Labor Battalions:</hi> Agreement reached that nothing
                            shld be mentioned in treaty itself this subj but that Bonn agreement on
                            phasing out labor battalions in Ger be placed in special
                            protocol.</item>
                        <label>4)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Natl Forces for Internatl Missions:</hi>
                            <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> wanted limitation to
                                <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> type missions; <persName
                                corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1">Hallstein</persName> said <gloss
                                target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> might require special contingents.
                            Agreement being reached on language to meet <persName
                                corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> point that, if <gloss
                                target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> wanted contingents for any purpose,
                            it shld request <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> and not natl govts
                            to furnish them.</item>
                        <label>5)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Voting Rights:</hi>
                            <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> argued that
                            consideration be given now to principle underlying computation of voting
                            rights and that mins shld not wait for Bonn decisions re Ger Fin
                            contributions. Problem postponed to end of agenda.</item>
                        <label>6)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Seat of Institutions:</hi>
                            <persName corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1">Hallstein</persName> requested
                            decision be postponed until after ratification <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                                >EDC</gloss> treaty by <gloss target="#t_FedRep1">FedRep</gloss>.
                            Probably will be taken up in June mtg <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                                >EDC</gloss> Mins when they plan discuss implications of <persName
                                corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> proposal RE Council of Eur and
                                <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> and <persName
                                corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> Plan.</item>
                        <label>7)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ratification:</hi>
                            <persName corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1">Hallstein</persName> said his govt
                            determined carry thru debate on <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>
                            before Parl vacation. <persName corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1"
                                >Stikker</persName> says Dutch ratification impossible before Dec at
                            earliest.</item>
                        <label>8)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Language:</hi> (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) Interim org
                            to consider languages to be used by Institutions of the Community.
                            Official languages will probably be same as those being considered by
                            Coal and Steel Community; i.e. Fr, Ger, Ital and Dutch. (<hi
                                rend="italic">b</hi>) Auxiliary language <gloss target="#t_EDF1"
                                >EDF</gloss>; to be decided by unanimous vote of Council, it being
                            understood that language will be English but with flexibility to permit
                            others to be used. Reason for this provision was that all agreed English
                            was desirable auxiliary language for <gloss target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss>
                            but that it wld be difficult to present to the <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                                >EDC</gloss> parls a text which required use of a language other
                            than that of the six countries. (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) Official text
                            of treaty will be in Fr but with authentic official translations in all
                            other <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> languages. In case of
                            discrepancies Fr will govern.</item>
                        <label>9)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Stationing <gloss target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss> Outside
                                Eur as Defined Art 6 <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss>:</hi> Mins
                            decided firmly against permitting <gloss target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss> to
                            be sent out of area defined Art 6 <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss>.
                                <persName corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName> stated he did
                            not wish <gloss target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss> to go anywhere where they
                            were not covered by UK and <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>
                            guarantees. <persName corresp="#p_VANZEELAND1">Van Zeeland</persName>
                            said he wld agree to enlarge area in which <gloss target="#t_EDF1"
                                >EDF</gloss> can be stationed to whole area covered in Art 6 <gloss
                                target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss>. Altho <persName
                                corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName> maintained that under
                                <persName corresp="#p_VANZEELAND1">Van Zeeland</persName> suggestion
                                <gloss target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss> cld be stationed in an area not
                                <pb facs="0709" n="665" xml:id="pg_665"/> covered by UK guarantee to
                                <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>, he said he wld think it over.
                            Mins decided to reconsider <persName corresp="#p_VANZEELAND1">Van
                                Zeeland</persName> suggestion and also, at <persName
                                corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName>’s urging, to reconsider
                            whether <gloss target="#t_EDF1">EDF</gloss> schools and training centers
                            might not by unanimous decision <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>
                            Council be installed outside Art 6 area.</item>
                        <label>10)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Duration of Treaty:</hi> Dutch ultimatum to effect
                            that unless other countries agree by tomorrow that <gloss
                                target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> treaty is only for 17 years; i.e.
                            identical in time with <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss>, or that
                            Dutch at least can pull out at that time, Dutch will not sign. <persName
                                corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName>, <persName
                                corresp="#p_TAVIANIPE1">Taviani</persName>, and <persName
                                corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1">Hallstein</persName>, particularly the
                            latter, insisted on 50 year duration. <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1"
                                >Schuman</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_HALLSTEINW1"
                                >Hallstein</persName> offered compromise along lines that, in case
                            of <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> change in membership, <gloss
                                target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> states wld consult. <persName
                                corresp="#p_STIKKERDU1">Stikker</persName> found this unacceptable
                            and said he had firm instrs not to sign treaty unless Dutch wld be free
                            to withdraw whenever US or UK defense guarantee no longer in force.
                            Question, he said, was whether it was desired to have Netherlands as
                            member <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> on this condition or to
                            conclude <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> treaty without Dutch
                            participation.</item>
                        <label>11)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ger Unification:</hi>
                            <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> said many Fr
                            Parliamentarians wondered how Ger unification wld affect both <gloss
                                target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> and <persName corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1"
                                >Schuman</persName> Plan, but discussion brief and no conclusions
                            reached.</item>
                        <label>12)</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="italic">
                                <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> Council Vote on Joint mtg with
                                    <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss> Council:</hi> Fr agreed
                            joint mtg of two Councils can be called by majority vote in <gloss
                                target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> Council.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
